Config, which would utilize defaults. I wonder if this could affect default sources. It's challenging to figure out what works best without assertions!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing resource handling**\\\\n\\\\nIf there's no meta resource, it will trigger getResource to read system properties. I need to assert that the default source reads the system prop appropriately. This setup could effectively cover getResource. In buildConfig, if meta=MpMetaConfig.metaConfig and no environment or system meta config is found, it will look for defaults, leading to getResource for YAML and properties. It seems that no resource is necessary for this. However, I wonder if setting the meta-config system property in the test might be beneficial, just in case the current directory has an mp-meta-config file.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering test class mapping**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about the one-to-one mapping for the test class named MpMetaConfigTest. I need to be careful not to compile or run anything at this stage. It might be a good idea to inspect the dynamic report to ensure that it only reflects the class. My goal is clarity and accuracy as I’m trying to make sure everything aligns correctly!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_9Us2kbCLqVNYIjjKULsVZOUe|fc_027a1594cf2c1d3d016a23717e46108195818d9cf3acaad84b\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/io.helidon.config/helidon-config-mp/4.3.4/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\", \"limit\": 100}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 806, \"output\": 1124, \"cacheRead\": 32256, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 34186, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780707684609, \"responseId\": \"resp_027a1594cf2c1d3d016a2371653fa88195b3a16a9